: > I know of no VCRs (certainly at least not mine) which will change the
: > channel on my cable box for scrambled programs requiring the box for
: > decoding (HBO, etc.).

:   The Mitsubishi U-69 can control a wide variety of cable boxes. It also 
: accepts VCR+ codes directly.

The Celadon PIC-100 can control upto sixteen infrared devices simultaneously,
it has an embedded realtime clock and can be programmed (loops, macros) by
the user.  It also comes with a serial interface to download or upload new
operating systems or programs.

